0.15    2017-01-12 (PERLANCAR)

	- Adjust to Perinci::CmdLine::Inline 0.47 ('my %_pci_metas' changed
	  to 'my $_pci_metas' line).


0.14    2017-01-12 (PERLANCAR)

	- Adjust to Perinci::CmdLine::Inline 0.45.


0.13    2017-01-09 (PERLANCAR)

	- Return parsed # PERICMD_INLINE_SCRIPT_METAS generated by
	  Perinci::CmdLine::Inline 0.42+.


0.12    2017-01-07 (PERLANCAR)

	- [Incompatible change] Rename function
	  detect_perinci_cmdline_script to detect_pericmd_script, we
	  standardize on the shorter name (old name is still around but
	  deprecated and undocumented).


0.11    2016-08-23 (PERLANCAR)

	- [Bugfix][regression] Forgot to detect 'require Perinci::CmdLine'
	  in addition to 'use Perinci::CmdLine'.


0.10    2016-08-11 (PERLANCAR)

	- [optimize] Avoid regex slowdown of detecting /^\s*use
	  Perinci::CmdLine/ due to \s* after ^, when source lines reach
	  many thousands, by splitting the source per line.


0.09    2016-03-16 (PERLANCAR)

	- No functional changes.

	- Replace JSON with JSON::MaybeXS.


0.08    2015-09-03 (PERLANCAR)

	- No functional changes.

	- [dist] Move spec prereqs from RuntimeRequires to
	  DevelopRecommends to reduce deps but still allow indicating spec
	  requirement.


0.07    2015-07-30 (PERLANCAR)

	- Support Perinci::CmdLine::Inline.

	- Tweak Rinci metadata for CLI.


0.06    2014-12-27 (PERLANCAR)

	- Respect # NO_PERINCI_CMDLINE_SCRIPT directive.


0.05    2014-11-05 (PERLANCAR)

	- [Incompatible change] Change interface so the function can accept
	  filename or string.


0.04    2014-11-01 (PERLANCAR)

	[REMOVED FEATURES]

        - Remove options 'include_backup' and 'include_wrapper'. The first one
          does not really belong in the function and the second one is feature
          creep and a misconcept. To accomplish wanted feature,
          App::BashCompletionF will be modified instead.


0.03    2014-11-01 (PERLANCAR)

	- Return extra data when detecting wrapper script.


0.02     2014-11-01 (PERLANCAR)

         [INCOMPATIBLE CHANGES]

         - Rename option 'filter_x' to 'include_noexec' to be more consistent
           with the other 'include_*' options.

         [ENHANCEMENTS]

         - Add options: 'include_backup', 'include_wrapper'.


0.01     2014-11-01 (PERLANCAR)

         - First release.
